---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageShell from "../../components/PageShell.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="History of the Club | Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC"
  description="The history of Wroughton Youth Football Club and its development into Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC."
>
  <PageShell>
    <section class="py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
        <a
          href="/about"
          class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-300 hover:text-blue-200"
        >
          ← Back to About
        </a>

        <div class="mt-10">
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-blue-300">
            Club History
          </p>

          <h1 class="text-5xl font-light tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">
            History of the Club
          </h1>

          <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
            <p>
              Wroughton Youth Football Club (WYFC) has been an important part of
              the local community since it was established in 1992. Based in the
              village of Wroughton, near Swindon in Wiltshire, the club was created
              to give children and young people the opportunity to play organised
              football in a safe, friendly and enjoyable environment. Over the years,
              the club has grown from a small grassroots setup into a thriving
              organisation with more than 400 players aged between 5 and 18.
            </p>

            <p>
              WYFC is affiliated with the Wiltshire County FA and competes in the
              North Wiltshire Youth Football League. The club has built a strong
              reputation for encouraging participation, teamwork and sportsmanship,
              while also helping young players develop their football skills and
              confidence. Many former youth players have progressed into adult
              football, strengthening the connection between WYFC and the
              long-established Wroughton men’s teams.
            </p>

              <p>
                In 2026, Wroughton Youth FC evolved into Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC, 
                marking a new, ambitious, chapter in the club's history. This change 
                reflects the club's expansion to serve the broader Wroughton and Wichelstowe 
                communities, while maintaining its commitment to providing inclusive 
                football opportunities for all ages and abilities, including Adult football. 
                The club continues to build on its strong foundations, with a focus on 
                community engagement, player development and creating a welcoming environment 
                for everyone who loves football. 
                As part of this transition, the club has also become a registered charity, 
                ensuring that its future growth and sustainability are supported by a strong 
                governance structure and community-focused values.
              </p>

            <p>
              The club is entirely run by dedicated volunteers, coaches and committee members
              who work hard to support the local community. Today, Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC
              continues to provide affordable & inclusive football opportunities for children 
              of all abilities and remains proud of its community values and football heritage.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </PageShell>
</Layout>